Peru Stocks: Candente, Cementos Lima, Ferreyros, IRL, Relapasa

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-12-09T23:03:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-09/peru-stocks-candente-cementos-lima-ferreyros-irl-relapasa.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m. Lima time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  was little changed at 19,985.96. The
 MSCI All Peru Capped Index  gained 0.9 percent to 2,565.75.  Mining stocks declined after copper and zinc fell this week
in  New York  and  London , said  Jorge Ramirez , a trader at Lima-
based brokerage Coril SAB.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian mining
exploration company with operations in Peru, dropped 4.3 percent
to $1.11.  Cia. Minera Milpo (MILPOC1)  (MILPOC1 PE), a zinc and silver
producer controlled by Sao Paulo-based Votorantim Metais Ltda.,
fell 1.4 percent to 4.83 soles.  Sociedad Minera El Brocal SAA 
(BROCALC1 PE), a zinc and silver producer, declined 0.5 percent
to 45.01 soles.  Minera IRL Ltd. (MIRL)  , a U.K. minerals explorer with a
gold mine in Peru, jumped 5.4 percent to $1.18, a two-month high,
after gold futures advanced in New York today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
